org.sindice.siren.analysis

Class JsonTokenizer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.lucene.util.AttributeSource

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class JsonTokenizer
extends org.apache.lucene.analysis.Tokenizer
    A tokenizer for data following the JSON syntax.

    The tokenizer parses JSON data and generates a token for each field name and each value. The tokenizer attaches a node label and a datatype to each token.

    Regarding datatype, the convention is the following:

    • If a field name is parsed, the datatype JSONDatatype.JSON_FIELD is assigned;
    • If a value string is parsed, the datatype XSDDatatype.XSD_STRING is assigned;
    • If a boolean value is parsed, the datatype XSDDatatype.XSD_BOOLEAN is assigned;
    • If a numerical value is parsed, the datatype XSDDatatype.XSD_LONG is assigned;
    • If a numerical value with a fraction is parsed, the datatype XSDDatatype.XSD_DOUBLE is assigned;
